    {
      "content": [
        {
          "text": "The configuration is the core of ",
          "type": "text"
        },
        {
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "bold"
            }
          ],
          "text": "Rime",
          "type": "text"
        },
        {
          "text": ", this is where you define how your documents will be structured, localization, panel access configuration, custom API routes and ",
          "type": "text"
        },
        {
          "marks": [
            {
              "attrs": {
                "class": null,
                "href": "#properties",
                "rel": "noopener noreferrer nofollow",
                "target": "_self"
              },
              "type": "link"
            }
          ],
          "text": "more",
          "type": "text"
        },
        {
          "text": "… The configuration entry ",
          "type": "text"
        },
        {
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "bold"
            }
          ],
          "text": "must be located at ",
          "type": "text"
        },
        {
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ],
          "text": "src/lib/config/rime.config.ts",
          "type": "text"
        },
        {
          "text": ". Here is a basic configuration example :",
          "type": "text"
        }
      ],
      "type": "paragraph"
    },
    {
      "attrs": {
        "language": "ts"
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "text": "// src/lib/config/rime.config.ts\r\nimport { buildConfig, Collection } from '$rime/config';\r\nimport { text } from '@bienbien/rime/fields';\r\n\r\nconst Pages = Collection.create('pages', {\r\n  fields: [\r\n    text('title').isTitle().required(),\r\n  ]\r\n});\r\n\r\nexport default buildConfig({\r\n  $database: 'my-app.sqlite'\r\n  collections: [Pages]\r\n});",
          "type": "text"
        }
      ],
      "type": "codeBlock"
    },
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Note that **server-only properties** are declared with the `$` prefix. This is because the configuration will be split into a client and server versions, **generated in the **`$lib/+rime.generated`** folder (location may change, but this setup ensures relative imports remain intact).**",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "type": "infoBlock"
    },
    {
      "attrs": {
        "level": 2
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "text": "Document prototypes",
          "type": "text"
        }
      ],
      "type": "heading"
    },
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "text": "There are two document prototypes : collections and areas. Collections are repeatable content type e.g. users, pages, products…, and areas are singletons e.g. navigation, footer, information…",
          "type": "text"
        }
      ],
      "type": "paragraph"
    },
    {
      "attrs": {
        "language": "ts"
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "text": "import { Collection, Area } from '$rime/config';\r\nimport { text, toggle } from '@bienbien/rime/fields';\r\n\r\nconst Settings = Area.create('settings', {\r\n  fields: [\r\n    toggle('maintenance')\r\n  ]\r\n});\r\n\r\nconst Pages = Collection.create('pages', {\r\n  fields: [\r\n    text('title').isTitle().required()\r\n  ]\r\n});",
          "type": "text"
        }
      ],
      "type": "codeBlock"
